The Representation of Gender in Ohio Universityâ€™s the Green Goat PART 3 of 3 By Kaleb Martin The third installment of â€œRepresentations of Gender in the Green Goatâ€ examines types of men which commonly appear in the humor magazine. Although a range of behaviors and stereotypes for men can be found within the Green Green, two which are most apparent are the Man as Amorous Opportunist and The Gentleman. Succinctly, the Gentleman tends to respect his partnerâ€™s boundaries, while the Amorous Opportunist is more concerned with fulfilling his own desires. They are portrayed as humorous characters for different reasons: the Amourous Opportunist is comical due to his persistent and shameless pursuit of female attention, while the Gentleman entertains readers by observing traditions and etiquette seen as â€œstuffyâ€ or outdated. Separate analyses of the two can be found below. 3. Â  Man as Amorous Opportunist (Figures 8 and 9) Within the pages of the Goat, comics and short stories often depict the male college students as the Amorous Opportunist, who seeks out any occasion to attempt to seduce women. He can be suggestive and sly or forward and shameless. Since the object of his affection is usually more cautious than he is, her boundaries predict the extent of the pairâ€™s activities. Â In figure 8, the male character leans towards his love interest, seeming to pull her closer to his body. She faces away from him, expressing her reticence. He verbally suggests his desirous intentions for her. Figure 9 provides another example of the innuendo and ulterior intentions of the Amorous Opportunist.Â  4. Â  The Gentleman (Figures 10 and 11) Seemingly the opposite of the Amorous Opportunist, the Gentleman finds himself in similar territory as the former, while maintaining his manners and romantic sensibilities. As in figure 10, he asks permission before making advances, often to the point of making his partner impatient. His sincerity matches his partnerâ€™s or contrasts with their flippancy. Figure 11 illustrates the whimsical prose of the gentleman contrasted with the indifference of his partner. The Gentleman can be understood to represent the tradition, etiquette, romantic norms of the nineteenth century. Read Part 1 and Part 2 of the 3 part series

Cara Menyembuhkan Kencing Nanah Secara Alami. Cara Menyembuhkan Kencing Nanah Secara Alami - Dalam menjalani kehidupan kita harus selalu selektif dan berhati-hati khususnya bagi mereka yang sudah dewasa dan melakukan hubungan intim. Dari pergaulan bebas tersebut akan menimbulkan berbagai jenis macam penyakit. Salah satunya adalah penyakit kencing nanah. Penyakit kencing nanah merupakan salah satu penyakit yang menyerang pada alat ï¿½ï¿½kelamin. Penyakit jenis ini tidak hanya menyerang kepada pria saja tetapi juga wanita. Memang bagi orang awam penyakit ini jarang terdengar karena memang penyakit ini lebih berpotensi terhadap mereka yang sudah berkeluarga. Penyakit ini disebabkan oleh bakteri jahat yaitu bakteri Neisseria gonohoea. Bakteri ini dapat menimbulkan kerusakan dan infeksi pada leher rahim, saluran kandung kemih, rectum tenggorokan dan bola mata. Penyakit kencing nanah ini termasuk penyakit yang menular. Penularan tersebut melaui beberapa macam cara baik itu dengan hubungan intim ataupun hal lainya. Dan perlu diperhatikan penyakit satu ini dapat menyebar keseluruh bagian tubuh melalui aliran darah. Oleh karena, penyakit satu ini merupakan penyakit yang cukup berbahaya. Gejala utama dari penyakit kencing nanah ini adalah keluarnya air nanah saat buang air kecil. Selain itu, gejala lain dari penyakit kencing nanah ini adalah air kencing berwarna kehijauaan, bertambahnya cairan dari vagina, terserang beberapa infeksi dibagian tubuh lalu susah untuk melakukan aktifitas sehari-hari. Bagi Anda yang merasakan penyakit tersebut jangan takut dan khawatir karena sekarang ini terdapat obat ampuh kencing nanah. Obat ampuh ini bukan obat biasa yang harus dengan harga mahal ataupun penggunaan teknologi canggih. Memang kita akui untuk jenis obat tersebut memilki khasiat yang cepat dan instant. Akan tetapi dibalik itu semua akan merasakan dampak yang cukup berbahaya. Berikut Sekilas Tentang Penyakit Kencing Nanah : Cara Mengatasi Kencing Nanah Pada Pria - Kencing nanah (Gonore) adalah penyakit menular seksual (PMS). Kencing nanah disebabkan oleh Neisseria gonorrhoea, bakteri yang dapat tumbuh dan berkembang dengan mudah pada saluran reproduksi yang hangat dan lembab, termasuk pada serviks (mulut rahim), uterus (rahim), dan tuba falopi (saluran telur) wanita, dan di uretra (saluran urin) wanita dan pria. Gonore menular melalui kontak dengan penis, vagina, atau anus. Tidak harus ada ejakulasi untuk terjadinya penularan atau terjangkitnya penyakit ini. kencing nanah juga dapat ditularkan ibu kepada anaknya selama kelahiran. Penyebab Penyakit Kencing Nanah : Hubungan Seksual secara Bebas Hubungan seksual yang dilakukan secara bebas merupakan faktor penyebab utama terinfeksinya penyakit ini. Hal ini karena hubungan seks yang dilakukan dengan cara berganti-ganti pasangan memungkinkan seseorang yang mengidap penyakit ini untuk meularkannya. Penularan penyakit kencing nanah akan berlanjut terus sebelum penderita berhenti melakukan hubungan seks bebas ataupun sembuh total. Aktivitas Seksual yang Tidak Sehat Hubungan seks bebas juga merupakan salah satu bagian dari aktivitas seksual yang tidak sehat, namun selain itu ada beberapa faktor lain yang juga ikut bepengaruh dalam penularan penyakit ini. Aktivitas seks lainnya diantaranya yaitu oral seks, anal seks, seks non penetratif dan aktivitas seksual lainnya. Ibu yang Melahirkan Seorang ibu yang mengidap penyakit ini dapat menularkan penyakit tersebut kepada Anaknya apabila melahirkan secara normal atau melalui vagina. Kebersihan organ Intim Kebersihan organ intim merupakan faktor kesehatan organ tersebut. Apabila organ tersebut tidak bersih, maka kemungkinan terkena berbagai penyakitpun sangat besar. Termasuk penyakit kencing nanah. Maka dari itu sangatlah perlu kita menjaga kebersihan organ intim. Kebersihan Pakaian Pakaian merupakan pelindung atau penutup tubuh yang digunakan sehari-hari oleh kita. Setiap pakaian yang kita kenakan haruslah bersih agar tubuh kita tidak mudah terkena penyakit termasuk kencing nanah, karena bakteri atau virus penyebab penyakit selalu ada di tempat-tempat yang kotor. Celana dalam merupakan pakaian yang harus selalu terjaga kebersihannya, dan peggunaannyapun harus sering diganti dengan yang bersih secara teratur. Karena jika tidak, pakaian tersebut dapat menjadi sarang berkumpulnya bakteri-bakteri atau virus penyebab penyakit. Kebersihan Linkungan Lingkungan merupakan tempat kita tinggal, termasuk rumah dan daerah tempat tinggal sekitar. Jika lingkungan tersebut tidak bersih atau sehat maka berbagai penyakit akan mudah datang dan menyerang. Maka dari itu sangatlah penting untuk selalu merawat dan menjaga kebersihan dan kesehatan lingkungan. Penyebab kencing nanah diatas merupakan faktor penyebab kencing nanah yang saya ketahui, maka dari itu sangatlah wajar jika ada penyebab kencing nanah lainnya yang tidak saya tuliskan dalam artikel ini. Untuk kejelasannya, saya sarankan Anda untuk menanyakan kepada dokter secara langsung. Gejala Penyakit Kencing Nanah : Pada pria, gejala awal penyakit kencing nanah biasanya timbul dalam waktu 2-7 hari setelah terinfeksi. Gejalanya berawal dengan rasa tidak nyaman pada uretra dan beberapa jam kemudian diikuti oleh nyeri ketika buang air kecil serta keluarnya nanah dari penis. Sedangkan pada wanita, gejala awal biasanya timbul waktu 7-21 hari setelah terinfeksi. Penderita seringkali tidak merasakan gejala selama beberapa minggu atau bulan, dan diketahui menderita penyakit tersebut hanya setelah pasangan hubungan seksualnya tertular. Jika penyakit kencing nanah menimbulkan gejala, biasanya bersifat ringan dan mendadak hilang dengan sendirinya. Tetapi beberapa penderita menunjukkan gejala yang berat, seperti desakan untuk berkemih, nyeri ketika berkemih, keluarnya cairan dari vagina, dan demam. Infeksi dapat menyerang leher rahim, rahim, saluran telur, indung telur, uretra, dan rektum serta menyebabkan nyeri pinggul yang dalam ketika berhubungan seksual. preprotext: Lizz Astor. Lizz Astor has just won Best Film for her short film Tank, at the Rehoboth Beach International Film Festival. Here, she writes us about the incredible experience. This weekend I voyaged to Rehoboth Beach, Delaware, a place I had driven and casually breezed through many a summer on the way to the beach. My best friend and I drove three hours from my home in Baltimore to arrive at this beautiful, sleepy, tax free beach town to attend the Rehoboth Beach International Film Festival, which had decided, of the numerous entries, I was the winner of their student film award (and a glorious $1,000) check. I guess I should start from the beginning. Last May I completed post production on my first year film, â€œTankâ€, a narrative short that centers around divorce. My intention with the film was to create something hauntingâ€“a soft violence, and to highlight how devastating it is to see your mom cry. I screened the film to my class, and to the â€˜publicâ€™ on our last day of freshman year, and then posted it on Vimeo/ Facebook. I was amazed at the response, which was overwhelmingly positive. People reached out to me, telling me how much the film resonated with them and felt exactly that experience with their own parentsâ€™ divorce. As a person whose parents are happily together, and even occasionally cute, this meant a lot. I got an email about Rehoboth from SVA and figured why not. It was free and it couldnâ€™t hurt. I mailed a form in and waited for an email, which came 2 months later. I received many emails from Denise, the outreach coordinator, which ranged from asking if I had the rights to the music I had used (which I quickly acquired), to finally one that simply read: Congrats!! She asked if I was available to come to the festival to receive the award and I, wanting any reason to get out of the city and also not wanting to pass up an opportunity, agreed. RBFF was a five-day festival that was split between two locations. I was impressed by how many bigger independent films they were showingâ€“a lot of things now playing at IFC center, or Sunshine. Even more amazing is that this was the case considering the RBFF demographic, which was all people over 55. I arrived on Saturday evening with my best friend in tow. We spent a considerable amount of time exploring the desolate beach, and exchanging smiles with the locals, walking their golden doodles down the boardwalk. I received a call from Denise saying that Andrew (the award benefactor) was around and would like to meet me if I have the time. Of course I agreed. I arrive at the â€˜big tentâ€™ to meet Denise face to face and Andrew for the first time. Denise is short and slender with a pretty pink lipstick. Andrew has a kind face and wears a scarf. He tells me I donâ€™t look like a girl who wants to sit in a heated tent and chat, and heâ€™s right. We walk to what he believes is a dive bar, but turns out to be an upscale restaurant with live entertainment and a martini bar. We get something to drink. He very generously pays. Andrew is Andrew Fierberg, a big time producer who has done films like Secretary, Fur, Keane, and about 30 other titles. He tells me about escaping to Brooklyn at the dawn of gentrification, working as a plumber, and launching Maggie Gyllenhalâ€™s career. He tells me things I need to hear like: you donâ€™t want to be a technician, you want to be an artist, and that he hates HD TV. An hour later we leave and he gives me his card, which I learn later is a big deal. He tells me to email him because he would love to help and he thinks Iâ€™m smart and promising. I am flattered. And that Sunday night I fall asleep with a $1,000 check listening to the waves lap onto the beach.

Wave Length. The Wavelength exhibition at the Auckland Art Gallery has been there for a while and I have seen it before. With the gained knowledge from BCT, I kept asking myselfï¿½ï¿½â€œHow did they make this?â€, trying to link it back to sensors and programming. Using a Kinect to capture movements and turn it into art. I donâ€™t know why but I couldnâ€™t help but silently laugh to myself when I saw the RGB lights. Speed Drill of the Day: Build Agility and Body Control with the T-Drill. The ability to stop and change directions quickly is critical to athletic success. The T-Drill is a simple cone drill that hones your ability to generate speed over a short distance and change directions effectively. The T-Drill forces you to sprint forward, backwards and side-to-side, all while constantly changing directions. It not only works on your speed and agility, but also your balance and body control. You can tweak the distance of the T-Drill to make it either more of a short agility drill or more of a longer, top-speed drill. How to Perform the T-Drill Arrange four cones into a T shape. The distance between the cones is up to you, but placing them somewhere between 5 and 8 yards apart is a good place to start. Begin at the cone at the bottom of the T. Sprint forward to the cone at the top center of the T. Breakdown and backpedal to the bottom cone. Breakdown and sprint back to the top center cone. Cutting either right or left, sprint to the cone in that direction (if youâ€™d like, you can have a partner point a direction to test your reactions). Breakdown and cut around that cone to switch directions and sprint to the farthest cone. Breakdown and cut around that cone to switch directions and sprint to the top middle cone. Make a crisp cut and sprint back through the bottom cone to finish the drill. Sets/Reps: 6-8 total reps, alternating the direction you run first This article originally appeared on STACK.com: Speed Drill of the Day: Build Agility and Body Control with the T-Drill

Image sourced from yurijay@instagram While it bears striking similarities to a certain other tower in a certain French city, the Tokyo Tower is a distinctive icon of none other than, the city of Tokyo (hence the name). Both an observation tower, and a communication tower, the Tokyo Tower is the second tallest artificial structure in all of Japan and one of the most iconic tourist destinations in Tokyo. Built in 1958, and inspired by the Eiffel Tower, the Japanese are never to be outdone as the Tokyo Tower is a whole 13 meters taller than the original. And while spectacular night scenes make the towers look even more similar, the Tokyo Tower is a distinctive red and white colour. However, this is apparently for aviation safety reasons and not aesthetic reasons and the colour is apparently â€œinternational red orange.â€ï¿½ï¿½ Image sourced from shunyoshiko@instagram As a huge city person, as they call it, Iâ€™m very familiar with the concept of iconic buildings or structure in cities. In fact, theyâ€™re one of my favourite things about cities. The Kamehameha statue is famous.ï¿½ï¿½ Every June 11th. on Kamehameha Day, this bronze statue, clothed in gold with an outstretched arm, is draped in Hawaiiâ€™s finest leisâ€¦plumeria, pekake, ginger, and tuberose decorate this striking figure.ï¿½ï¿½ This statue is located near downtown Honolulu and I must have driven past it one hundred timesâ€¦so today I decided to take a closer look and share it with you! Standing directly in front of the Ali'iolani Hale, Hawaiiâ€™s Judiciary History Center and Supreme Court, and across the street from the Iolani Palace, stands Kamehameha, Hawaiiâ€™s ruler from 1782 until 1819.ï¿½ï¿½ Considered the Guardian of the God of War, Kamehameha was best known for his humanitarian efforts.ï¿½ï¿½ His grand gesture, holding a spear in one hand and reaching out to his people with the other showed the artistâ€™s European flare, as it was a pose used commonly by Roman generals.ï¿½ï¿½ Commissioned in 1878 by a member of the Hawaii government, this 14-foot statue was sculpted in Italy and then sent to Paris, France to be cast in bronze.ï¿½ï¿½ In 1883 the statue was shipped to Hawaii - but it didnâ€™t arrive.ï¿½ï¿½ The ship carrying this precious cargo was shipwrecked near the Falkland Islands.ï¿½ï¿½ Can you imagine? Shipwrecked! Luckily the statue was insured for $12,000 - an exorbitant amount of money at the time - and a new one was quickly cast.ï¿½ï¿½ Before the second statue could be shipped from Europe, fishermen in the Falkland Islands found the first statue.ï¿½ï¿½ It was sold back to the Captain of the wrecked ship for $500â€¦the crafty Captain then turned around and sold it immediately back to Hawaiiâ€¦for $875! Now Hawaii has TWO statues!ï¿½ï¿½ The original statue can be located at Kamehamehaâ€™s birthplace on the big island of Hawaii and the second commissioned piece is here on Oahuâ€¦in the heart of Honolulu! ï¿½ï¿½ 137 years later there are now six Kamehameha statues but that is another storyâ€¦ -Meredith Novack

HHA Theme Challenge: Harmonious ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ how I reached 1.3m points IF YOU HAVENâ€™T COMPLETED ALL INTERIOR CHALLENGES, DO NOT START THE THEME CHALLENGE! I missed out on getting the gold model home bc I started my theme challenge before reaching the 300k point marker. According to this gamefaqs thread, once you start your theme challenge it overrides any interior prizes you still havenâ€™t won. So please be sure to have reached 300k before starting your theme challenge! You can start it at ANY time by talking to Lyle in Nookâ€™s Homes. click the pictures for prominent furniture sets/series, and room location First off, Iâ€™ve been told by a lot of people that itâ€™s way easier to accomplish this feat by picking the fairy-tale theme. But I swore to not have a mermaid exterior, and Iâ€™d already fallen in love with my Cabana/vacation room and the refurbished Exotic series. Plus, I happen to really love the Zen exteriors, so this all worked out! IMO itâ€™s best if you go with whatever theme you ultimately want your exteriors to fall under, as those are the hardest and most annoying to get. USING GUIDES I struggled my ass off trying to figure out which furniture sets were Harmonious. There are a lot of awesome websites out there (ac wikia, moridb, thonky), but PLEASE try to cross check information! Thonky had alpine listed under Harmonious, but when I put it in my back room, my score dropped from ~990k to ~500k. My advice (which requires patience) is to check your score, add A COUPLE of furniture items from a series/set in ONE room, and the next day check with Lyle to see if your score goes up or down. If it goes down, you know it doesnâ€™t fit your theme, If it goes up, then youâ€™re good to go. I wasted half a lifetime refurbishing the Alpine series only to not need it. Some series are also a mystery!! Since Lyle doesnâ€™t actually break down your points earned, I have NO CLUE if the Rococo or Cabin series count as Harmonious. As of right now, my score is ~1.3m. According to every guide I used, Rococo fell under Antique/Fairy-Tale and the Cabin series was Rustic. I donâ€™t think I would be capable of reaching that high of a score with TWO rooms not fitting the theme. My advice is to attain the Exotic series, Cabana series, and Zen/Zen Garden sets first. FURNITURE FILLERS So youâ€™ve completed your series and sets, but donâ€™t know what else to fill your room with? Bonsai are your best friend! And they help with your feng shui if you put the green ones on your southern-most walls (Jasmine bonsai should go to the left, and Maple bonsai should go to the right). All bonsai trees fall under the Harmonious theme, and they seem to mesh well with just about all the rooms. If you already have a cluster of favorite items (for me, I couldnâ€™t let go of my Dala horse or Skeleton Figurine), just check moridb to see what theme it falls under! I certainly didnâ€™t clear out EVERY single non-Harmonious item in my rooms, but it really does help in the long run to have as little as possible. After all, if 90% of your room falls under the theme, you get even more points. (For a room with the full 48 items, this means only 4-5 items can be non-Harmonious). YOU CAN CHANGE YOUR THEME AT ANY TIME If you really hate the direction your house is going, you can always change your theme by talking to Lyle. But ultimately, the house you design to reach 1.1m points does NOT have to be your dream house. I can tell yâ€™all right now I knew from day one that I was gonna scrap my zen room, but I put up with it bc I knew it was going to help me get the amount of points I needed. Donâ€™t change your theme bc you really hate ONE room. Just be patient, and know that once you get to 1.1m, you can scrap your entire house if thatâ€™s what your lil heart desires! Just have fun and experiment away! Towards the end of this challenge, I felt like it was such a chore, but it doesnâ€™t have to be that way. If you take the time to really explore your furniture options and pick a theme you really like, it will feel so rewarding.

Who proceeds to shoot fire at his mummy, forcing her to climb on his back, fly the heck out of Meereen and completely vanish until literally the final chapter of the book when she turns up in the Dothraki Sea. And obviously, he will not be doing any of that in the show. Because heâ€™s dead. But who could take over? Daario? Yes, its possible. Could Jorah make it back? Well he is on his way, and his show-only greyscale infection could be a parallel for the bloody flux, or even a parallel with the cut greyscale-infected character Jon Connington rushing to secure the rule of his favourite cut-from-the-show-maybe-Targaryan. Missandei? Sheâ€™s the only one of Danyâ€™s advisors left practically, and it sure would be interesting to see her handling real power for the first time in her life. But thereâ€™s another character whose show fate I am wondering about. Tyrion. In the books, Tyrion does sort of make it to Meereen, but only after he, Jorah and Penny (who the show has cut) are captured by slavers and wind up in the Yunkaiâ€™i camp outside the walls. However, Tyrion and Jorah arenâ€™t at sea anymore, so the capture seems less likely. Also, it doesnt seem like Yunkai is actually going to attack Meereen in the show, the Sons of the Harpy are the only threat the city is facing - so Tyrion canâ€™t end up in their camp. And anyway, we have this on set photo that suggests he is actually going to get to meet and be accepted by Daenerys. In fact, this looks rather like it could be the day of the fighting pit incident. Suggesting Tyrion will be there at the exact moment someone needs to take command. With no capture by slavers, no Yunkaiâ€™i attack, no Victarion Greyjoy with his dragonbinding horn, and no bloody flux, Iâ€™m kind of lost as to what Tyrionâ€™s storyline is going to be once he makes it to Dany. But of those problems the only one Tyrion would face is the Sons of the Harpy crisis - and of course we still donâ€™t know exactly what will happen with Dany, as when the books leave off she is ill, stranded in the middle of nowhere, and has been found by one of her old Dothraki enemies. We donâ€™t know if she will ever make it back to Meereen. But I wouldnâ€™t be surprised if Tyrion gets a lot of power and control in the Slavers Bay plot. Whatever Barristanâ€™s role would have been - I suspect it is going to end up falling to him.

How to Time Training Peaks to Be Your Best When It Matters Most. All your hard work should culminate when you peak for key competitions. Timing training peaks simply means adjusting your training in anticipation of performing at your highest level when it matters most. Training too hard before a competition can cause fatigue and suboptimal performance. Training too little can cause skills and fitness to deteriorate prematurely. During this phase, you make subtle changes to the training load that allow your body to take advantage of the cumulative effect of training and increase skill development while maintaining necessary fitness levels. In a typical 12-week season or training cycle, the peaking phase should start three to four weeks before the most important competitions. The shorter the season or training cycle, the shorter the peaking phase. A peaking phase can still include competitions. If your key competition is a state championship, your peaking phase will include the playoffs or sectionals. Training Peak Timing In the Weight Room To decease soreness and stiffness, phase out all non-compound movement lifts like Leg Presses and Curls. You shouldnâ€™t be doing these anyway. To sharpen coordination and balance, phase in bodyweight exercises. Check out the video player above for a demonstration. Increase the time between lifting sessions. If you are lifting three days per week, cut it to two. Instead of lifting Monday, Wednesday and Friday, lift Monday and Wednesday to take full advantage of this adaptation for weekend competitions. You can still train heavy with compound movements. Keep the intensity high. On the Track or Field Cut back both density and volume that culminates with 25- to 50-percent reductions. Phase in more intensity and purpose. Practices now are more about quality of reps than quantity. Phase in more restorative and mobility exercises to recover from the increased intensity and purpose. Well-spaced, short, intense practices are sufficient to maintain fitness and allow for additional recovery. Timing training peaks requires maintaining a delicate balance. If your peaking phase has been carefully planned, you should feel energized and full of anticipation. You will be ready to perform to the best of your ability. You are kind of unique in that you actively try to include a diverse cast of characters in your project. Why do you think most developers do not? -IK. Including a diverse cast is scary. It goes against the proven model. Big developers have proven that they can slap in Angry White Man or some large-chested women in a catsuit and sell millions of copies. Will gamers play as a heavier, middle-aged woman? Will gamers play as a black woman? These these are unknowns and unknowns are scary. The audience for games has diversified in recent years, but no one is really sure if this new audience has the buying power to carry a game. And no one is really sure how much of theï¿½ï¿½â€œtraditionalâ€ audience youâ€™ll lose with atypical lead characters. So thereâ€™s a lot of financial risk involved in trying to make a diverse game. Trying to be diverse also opens you up to criticism both for being too diverse and for not being diverse enough. Literally, in my Tumblr inbox, I have a post telling me Aberford sucks because it has too many minority characters, and two messages later someone tells me that Aberford sucks because I didnâ€™t include enough minority characters. Neither criticism has anything to do with the gameplay or the story. Theyâ€™re simply a side effect of trying to be inclusive and that scares developers. Weâ€™re just trying to make a small game with our own money plus about half a million dollars in funding. I canâ€™t imagine the risk that a company spending $100 million perceives when asked to be different. Diversifying a game also opens you up to a criticism about the quality of your diversification (a problem that doesnâ€™t exist if you stick with the proven model). People want to be represented in games, but they donâ€™t want to be misrepresented or portrayed in a way that they feel is negative. Thereâ€™s extra pressure in creating underrepresented characters, because theyâ€™re often viewed as a statement on the group at large. Any flaw or weakness (or lapse is writing quality) is viewed as a criticism of the group that character represents. Look at Black Widow in Age of Ultron. Is it possible that years of guilt and psychological trauma and showing pretend feelings instead of real ones, combined with seeing her best friendâ€™s beautiful children (that sheâ€™ll never have) and Mark Ruffaloâ€™s naked body (that she really wanted), make Natasha get all weird about her inability to have children? Probably. It was clumsy, but it wasnâ€™t absurd. It was a story that, with time to flesh it out, could have really worked for that character. However, because sheâ€™s the only woman on the team, her story has to stand for all women. Her stories have to fit a certain expectation, and if they donâ€™t, they end up alienating the very group they were supposed to connect with. If Nerd God and long-standing feminist Joss Whedon can get intensely flamed over a misstep, what hope to we sorry excuses for writers have? Plus, it takes a lot of work. Writing an angry white male is easy because the precedents are many and the expectations are low. Writing real female characters takes effort. Writing characters of color takes effort. Writing trans gender characters takes effort. And it opens you up to the risk of being a commercial or critical failure for reasons that have nothing to do with the actual quality of the game youâ€™ve made. So you really have to want to do it, and you have to really have the financial and creative freedom to do it, and thereâ€™s not a lot of devs that fit that bill. If weâ€™re not successful in our Kickstarter, we wonâ€™t fit that bill either.ï¿½ï¿½ TLDR: diversifying games carries a high financial risk and only really rewards you with the satisfaction of doing the right thing, which banks do not accept as payment. And if you mess it up: PAINFUL, AGONIZING FAILURE! (Shown below) So, if you want to see gaming get more diverse, try and support developers who are making the effort. Help them understand what to do (like you all have done for us) and be patient with their limitations. Keep pushing, obviously, but remember that itâ€™s an industry learning something new. Help them help you.

Mumbai Diaries #2. Mission - Find a Nest in Mumbai 6th April 2015, Silver Metropolis Auto-Stand Tiresome day at office, lot of formalities. The heart asked to Go-To guest house & take a nap. The mind said RUNâ€¦ Grab a home!!! Met a broker, shown us some truly, amazinglyâ€¦ PATHETIC squares. Oh wait they called those houses. Pardon meâ€¦â€¦â€¦â€¦.. I wanted to RUN AWAYâ€¦ from Mumbai. Once came the thoughtâ€¦ â€œIs it possible to commute everyday from Vadodara?â€ I may survive the travel of 6 hours-a-side but canâ€™t survive a moment in these â€¦â€¦ houses??? 2nd dayâ€¦ 3rd dayâ€¦ 4th dayâ€¦ Fridayâ€¦ WEEKENDâ€¦ The whole week passed in the quest to search a decent accommodation. Met 16 brokers, talked to about 35 owners, saw about 29 houses. Nothing worked. I had been to many cities, stayed there, none is like Mumbai. Here the Rent asked was not matching the class of the House. Specially when I straight-away came out of a just 1 year-old built, cozy, comfortable, lavish apartment - owned by my Dad. 12th April 2015, Dindoshi Bus Depot, Goregaon (E) - 12.10 PM I came here at 10.55 AM, waiting for any BEST bus to Mira Road. Buses to all routes are seen, not Mira road. Oh by the way, the search for a DECENT home is taking me to Mira road. 12th April 2015, Mc. Donalds Restaurant - 2.45 PM How can be two Indians have so different tastes??? AÂ â€˜TASTEFULLYâ€™ re-designed, 360 square feet, 1 room-kitchen converted to a 1-BHK; tasted so bad & choking to me that I almost puked at 700 meter away Mc. D. Ahhâ€¦ what a relief. God bless the Holy soul of Richard Mc. Donald for creating so tasty Burgers. So, I returned to my guest house by the evening, with no-success in finding a Nest (intentionally omittedÂ â€˜DECENTâ€™). 13th to 18th April 2015, Goregaon to Andheri to Borivali - Across the streets of Mumbai No gain, with so much of pain. No success in finding a decent Square BLOCK - yes I degraded myself from a Decent nest to a Nest to a Decent Square Block. So, what was the problem??? Ummmâ€¦ Some rooms were not sized enough to accommodate me, some were sized but not clean enough, some were seeking VEGGIE tenants, some wanted huge depositsâ€¦ And some asked for an EXORBITANT ransomâ€¦ I mean rent. 19th April 2015 - 10.30 AM - Dindoshi Bus Depot Today is my last day at the Guest House & in the evening Iâ€™m moving into my Uncleâ€™s place, in a nearby area. Nothing positive till now & I am boarding a bus to Kandivali east. Yesterday talked with a broker & he assured me to find something at reasonable. 19th April 2015 - 2.40 PM, Brokerâ€™s Office After seeing 7 houses today & 83 houses in total, of different physical & chemical properties, finally I convinced myself to settle for one of the options seen today at number-2. Paid the exorbitantly high deposit for a negligibly furnished, 15-20 years old apartment at a nice locality. Yes, that is why I convinced myself to settle for this. One of my friend, who lives in New York, told me once you can buy a mansion in theÂ â€˜Heart of New Yorkâ€™ with the same money, you canâ€™t buy a 3 BHK is south Mumbai. Mumbai, a really amazing city. Where 85% of the land is covered by illegal slums. A city where a billionaire wakes up in his lavish apartment on 25th floor, goes to the balcony to be greeted by a rehabilitated slum-dweller brushing his teeth with a twig. Because the same builder who built this lavish apartment had to rehabilitate the slum-dwellers into a box-sized SRA building, just adjacent to the billionaireâ€™s nests. Mumbai - the city of DREAMSâ€¦ But the biggest IRONY is, MUMBAI never SLEEPS. I will share some weird, funny, horrific, spine-chilling experiences in this city in my next post. Till then catch your breath. Because, I got a accommodation, to be possessed after 15 days, till then moved into my Uncleâ€™s house. And none the less, God had sent my this uncle to save me from becoming aÂ â€˜Home-Lessâ€™ for sometime. I shall be grateful to him, ever & forever. Because, very less often we cross someone of so much kindness. And whenever, we cross them. We should treasure them for LIFE. Nothing in life can pay-off this gesture. Is Nessie Really an Otter!?!?. From its tail to its characteristic hump and smooth, dinosaur-like head, it looks every inch like Scotlandâ€™s favorite monster. But one expert claims this photo is proof that Nessie is probably a much smaller and more common creature. On close inspection, the three â€˜humpsâ€™ are revealed to be the head, back and tail of an otter. The image was taken by Dr Jonathan Wills, off Lerwick in Shetland, and is of a female otter known locally as Dratsie. Her head, back and tail form three very distinctive humps which, at a distance could be mistaken for a much larger creature. Dr Wills says the image taken this week proves the beast said to prowl the depths of Loch Ness, hundreds of miles away, is more likely a 4ft otter than a monster.

Place in a large bowl. Mash. Cool completely. Step 2 â€“ Add salmon, corn, chives, parsley and lemon rind to potato. Stir to combine. Use 1/3 cup mixture at a time to make 8 patties. Step 3 â€“ Place flour on a plate. Place breadcrumbs on a plate. Whisk egg and milk together in a shallow dish. Coat 1 patty in flour, shaking off excess. Dip in egg mixture. Coat in breadcrumbs. Sanzo is as much of hard-ass due to his personality as well as because of the things in life that have hardened him. One of his weaknesses is that when he does care, he cares A LOT. My personal conclusion leads me to believe that for Sanzo it is very surprising that anyone wants to get close to him (generally speaking) despite him being up front about keeping himself distanced. His natural reaction to more directly continue to drive them off, but eventually if the other party keeps trying he will warm up to them. The man is hard-headed and stubborn by nature so â€œgiving inâ€ is not an easy thing but it does happen. This is what happens in this episode, as Sanzo is surprised the kitty brings him matches for his cigarette (thatâ€™s one heck of a smart kitty!) . He doesnâ€™t want her getting close but you can tell heâ€™s starting to accept the kitty does care for him whether he likes it or not. We also get proof why Sanzo should ~never~ be allowed in a kitchenâ€¦.Anyways, milk over boils, kitty jumps into the safety of Sanzoâ€™s arms and despite all that they take a nap together (all together nowâ€¦â€awwwwâ€). Isnâ€™t she the just happiest kitty when next to the grumpy blonde? xD; But the big kicker comes when youkai get into the room to attack Sanzo, the kitty jumps to defend him and gets seriously injured. Sound familiar? The only thing that could possibly have struck Sanzo in a milli-second is this was exactly how his Master Komyou Sanzo defended him, got struck down and killed. Thatâ€™s why Sanzo is telling the kitty to hang on and when it seems sheâ€™s not gonna make it, Sanzo looses it. A small incident that reminds him in seconds of one of the most marking events in his life, of course itâ€™s â€œunforgivableâ€ to let it repeat and thatâ€™s why heâ€™s beyond pissed that in fact he goes into his â€œcold heartedâ€ mode when he is absolutely merciless. Iâ€™m not saying heâ€™s never â€œnotâ€ cold hearted but moments like these that push him over the edge. Iâ€™m reminded of the desert chapter heâ€™s tortures the cross-dressing youkai and forgets â€œwhat is like to beâ€ himself. Good thing for his companions being there to snap him out of those moments. As the episode draws to a close and theyâ€™re outside the vet hospital, who of allï¿½ï¿½ but of all people should happen be holding the basket with the kitty? SANZO OF COURSE! He certainly doesnâ€™t seem quite like his usual selfâ€“ hell heâ€™s worriedâ€¦just LOOK at his face! â€œAnd thatâ€™s why I said we shouldnâ€™t bring her alongâ€¦â€ he says. Itâ€™s a dangerous journey. Asides the four of them that absolutely have to go on this journey, bringing along anyone else would be quite difficult and dangerous. Not being able to theoretically protect someone you care about so much itâ€™s quite a difficult emotion to deal with. So a lot of conflicting emotions hidden in this episode. But in the end, where Sanzo felt guilty that the kitty had gotten hurt, he can feel relief because she calls out (or rather meows out) to him and smiles. She still likes him the most and is happy to haveï¿½ï¿½â€œmet himâ€ before going back to her owner. That surprises our Sanzo but he accepts it some can actually like him, which is why we get this small but nonetheless, a warm smile. So why does Sanzo not like cats? It has been left up to individuals to determine what notion of virtues fit into their lives, along with the liberty to formulate a fitting sense of the right and good. Trust has deteriorated between so many people, and between people and those institutions that serve a meaningful democracy. Communal resources are increasingly being redirected into privatized pools through austerity measures largely serving market expansion and military development. ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ The daily practice for MacIntyre, in a neo-Aristotlian sense, is a political one. â€œWhat matters at this stage is the construction of local forms of community within which civility and the intellectual and moral life can be sustainedâ€¦â€ (2012; 263). This statement could just as easily apply to a committing oneself to a church community, a commune like Plum Village, or an anarcho-syndicalist community revitalizing a section of urban decay. The purpose of ethics in MacIntyre is clear, to transition â€œman-as-he-happens-to-be and man-as-he-would-be-if-he-realized-his-essential-nature.â€ That nature toward flourishing is interdependently reliant, or interdependently reasoned. Stout charts a course for understanding a form of postmodern theology, where theology is rid of modern trappings and present in ethical discourse in a meaningful way, no longer relegated to matters of religion alone. Of course Theology is a method apart from, but inclusive of religion. A theology that is freed from the normal discourse of religion can initiate dialog with teleological disruptors inherent to rapidly transforming bio-technologies and transmuting biological sciences. Keeping to predictable party lines for or against scientific developments and cultural shifts hinders theologyâ€™s special capacity for engaging with the transfiguration of human beings and shaping modes in ways that would be fruitful to the common good. Where MacIntyre dials his ethics in on the interpersonal dimensions of sustaining the virtues, Stout expands the aperture. There is a global ethics that can emerge from Stoutâ€™s analysis that courses the topology of liberal terrain, reacting positively where ever good social orders have broken ground and raised up. His is a kind of â€˜enlightened rationalismâ€™ that seeks the ability of humanity to achieve goods as it moves forward, and union through the spread of democratic ideals that foster the kind of representation that gives voice to commonly recognized goods. The Enlightenment was not an entire bust, at best it demands that we â€˜have courage to use our own reason,â€™ not for private use but for the individual in public use. At worst, while its perversions are not entirely novel to the age the effects of self-determination can cast ruin more coldly and more broadly due to the new economic and technological tracts global capitalism. Postmodernism renounces the modern commitment to reason having lived through its history of destructive applications to science, persistent high casualty warfare, holocausts, and genocides. Liberalism in this sense is a pragmatic response to the violence and suffering engendered by largely ideological conflict divides over who counts as persons and who doesnâ€™t, or whose lives matter. Liberalism demonstrates how more people flourish when a more inclusive sense of rights and obligations is drawn out of rhetoric and put to action, e.g. the civil rights movement, environmentalist movement, and LGBTQ movement. Stoutâ€™s positive argument for aspects of life in the ruptured social sphere along with his defense of theologyâ€™s place in social, political, and cultural discourse more broadly, emboldens the concrete truth that reforms large and small can an do occur, effectively lifting life up and out of darkness. But MacIntyre also seems right that we should be weary of thinking terms that go too far beyond the complex of our daily lives in community. The political state bears down on our lives through identity. Markets capture our desires at the point of identity, and as individuals we are like outcasts without the protection of our human value, which can only be sustained by virtue of our social bodies sustained by our deepest desires fulfilled in relation with each other. ~Robert Schmaltz Bibliography Lawrence S. Bosses of Bloodborne [PART 1]. After a long and arduous semester, Iâ€™m finally getting around to writing Bloodborne content for this blog. Letâ€™s just get started without any further delay! For each boss in the game, Iâ€™ll share both my first impressions and my later reflections. The former is pretty self-explanatory; the latter can range from atmosphere to design to hard mechanics â€“ whatever strikes me most strongly. Iâ€™ll try, as I usually do, to keep it varied and interesting. For the sake of tidiness and convenience, Iâ€™ve relegated everything to beneath the Moon. This first post will discuss Vicar Amelia and all bosses that can be fought prior to her, with the exception of Darkbeast Paarl. Enjoy! Cleric Beast My first foray against the Cleric Beast was actually pretty disappointing, though I was very impressed by the aesthetic design of the boss and the bridge arena. I defeated the Cleric Beast in my first attempt â€“ and though I attribute some of my success to skill and planning, a good portion of it was due to the fact that the boss hardly knew what it was doing. The Cleric Beast just floundered about for most of the fight, swiping at walls and obstacles more than it ever attempted to hit me. Once it just decided to leap to the far end of the bridge, away from my character. The poor thing just seemed bewildered and confused. I suspect now that this odd behavior was caused by the memory leak glitch that affected the game prior to patch 1.03, but it was pretty funny at the time. Now, having fought the Cleric Beast as it was meant to be fought, I rather like this fight. Itâ€™s large and intimidating, itâ€™s iconic, itâ€™s just aggressive enough for new players, and it imparts a sense that all is not impossible. Overall, itâ€™s a great introduction to the combat of Bloodborne. Moreover, the fact that itâ€™s optional allows more seasoned players, who wouldnâ€™t benefit from this fight in the same way that new players do, to skip amateur hour and cut straight to Father Gascoigne. Father Gascoigne My immediate impression of Father Gascoigne â€“ which subsequent playthroughs have only strengthened â€“ was that the good reverend marked a return to the tight, straightforward combat that characterized most of the humanoid bosses in the first Dark Souls. He kept me on my toes the entire time, especially since I neglected to use the music box during my first fights against him. I had collected it from his daughter, but for whatever reason I forgot to use it during combat. Adrenaline, I suppose. Piecing his story together posthumously was one of my favorite parts of Bloodborne. Unlike many other Souls bosses â€“ who are built up and hinted toward well before the fight itself â€“ Gascoigne is fought at a point when not much information is available to the player. Not even the Healing Church is very well known at this time. Piecing Gascoigneâ€™s life story together is something like a forensic investigation â€“ and it happens over the course of the entire game, so that the player really feels the weight of what he/she did well after he/she killed Father Gascoigne. Itâ€™s not like Astraea, who assaults the player with guilt during the fight itself, or Artorias, whose reputation is built up so high only to be subverted. Here, the playerâ€™s emotional understanding of this (initially) very frustrating boss changes after he/she has vented all of that frustration on him, and felt good doing so. Just when you thought that you had figured out every branch of their plotline, Gascoigne and his family once make you feel the weight of your own ignorance. And so the boss fight continues to be emotionally impactful even towards the end of the game. Blood-Starved Beast Before I learned its moveset, fighting the Blood-Starved Beast was one of the most frantic and bewildering boss fights that Iâ€™ve run across in a Souls game. I never found the boss particularly difficult or frustrating, but VERY frantic and fast-paced. Watching that thing leap around just aboutï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ gave me a heart attack! It was probably the first boss that forced me into the aggressive mentality that Miyazaki and FromSoftware wanted to encourage with Bloodborne. Not much to say beyond that, really. I do, however, like the implication that this beastâ€™s blood was drained as part of an attempted chalice ritual. The poison status effect might initially seem like a tacked-on gimmick, and it felt so at first â€“ but Iâ€™ve since realized the sheer brilliance of it, in the scheme of the gameâ€™s overall design. Prior to this point in the game, itâ€™s feasible that the player could have used blood vials and the regain system to squeeze by without having cultivated a good sense of dodging and timing. The slow poison effect puts an end to all that. Here, as Bloodborne enters the pace that it will maintain for most of the game, it forces players to learn a core skill that they will need in all future areas â€“ because if they donâ€™t, theyâ€™ll die from poison inflicted by telegraphed combos and glancing blows that could easily have been avoided. The Witch(es) of Hemwick I visited Hemwick after defeating Amelia, actually. In fact, in my first playthrough, I did absolutely nothing between the Blood-Starved Beast and Vicar Amelia â€“ but Iâ€™ll save the details for that bossâ€™s entry. Anyway! The Witches of Hemwick felt like a pleasant blend of the Foolâ€™s Idol, Pinwheel, and Dark Sun Gwyndolin. Theyâ€™re a fun â€œpuzzle boss,â€ with creative use of additional enemies. Not once did I feel frustrated while fighting this dual boss, despite the fact that I died twice to them, because it was interesting. It followed a principle that was largely ignored by the Dark Souls II team â€“ that when multiple enemies comprise a boss fight, those enemiesâ€™ respective designs and AIs should be made specifically to complement the other enemies in the boss arena. I also appreciate that, like Pinwheel, the Witches of Hemwick guard a near-necessary component of character/game progression â€“ and so theyâ€™re not difficult in any straightforward sense. Vicar Amelia Oh, Ameliaâ€¦ The first time I defeated her, it was with a +3 Threaded Cane, rather low Vitality, and 30+ deaths under my belt. Vicar Amelia was the first boss in Bloodborne to stop me dead in my tracks â€“ and it was largely my own doing. Prior to my first serious attempt at killing her, I had explored the area to the right of the Grand Cathedral. After several long and arduous fights, leading to a confusing dead-end, I assumed that the areas to the side of the Grand Cathedral were meant for a later time. So I did not visit Hemwick, nor did I acquire any of the vital blood echoes and upgrade materials to be gained there. The result was a frustrating slog against this hideous poodle-deer, in which I could whittle her down to her last eighth of health reliably and consistently â€“ but would inevitably fail when a glancing blow stunlocked me into a deadly combo, or when her healing undid all of my hard work. Out of pride, I did the equivalent of demolishing a brick wall by repeatedly smashing my head against it. There was no dignity in my victory, but there was much joy. Now, having learned a better route for character progression, Amelia is one of the easiest bosses for me to defeat; I take pleasure in cutting her down. I can appreciate how Amelia requires the player to use nearly all of the skills that had been cultivated one-at-a-time through other bosses. I can also appreciate how the fight against her rewards the player for taking a varied approach, dealing near-equal damage to each of her body parts. And I can also appreciate from firsthand experience what an obnoxious, repulsive bitch she is â€“ â€œbitchâ€ here meaning â€œugly female dogâ€ as much as it means â€œenormous pain in my ass.â€

preprotext: Thank You, Ellie Mobbs. Iâ€™ve had a tough year in radio, weâ€™ve all had one before and this is how I remembered I need to power through; because radio is in me. Growing up I never planned on being a radio announcer. Shy as hell, awkward to talk to and just plain not outgoing. At some point during primary school my mum told me I couldnâ€™t be shy anymore, I need to get through life and getting through would mean speaking up. That obviously hit hard and afterwards I became very chatty to those I considered buddies, but to this day I get painfully shy at times. That awkward little red head is still inside wondering â€œis that the right thing to say?â€ When I left high school I went to uni to study psychology, I knew I could talk to people, I knew I could talk someone down off a ledge if I needed to. But I also realised I wanted to be someone people could laugh with, and at. My friends growing up would say how funny I was and how I need to be a comedian. Iâ€™m not comedian funny though, I am me funny. So, when in uni, I tried a day of actingâ€¦ I soon realised prancing around the room with arms flailing and â€œletting go of every anxietyâ€ was not for me (yes, this isnâ€™t just what they do in the movies.) It was my words, my soul and my communication that was what I wanted heard but not necessarily seen. So I landed on radio and with the help of everyone around me got straight into my new life. Interestingly enough when I was in school I wrote an English assignment, it was a radio exchange between an announcer and the person from the play we were studying; an interview. I found it years later and itâ€™s the only 100% grade I ever received. I also found notes exchanged between me and a girlfriend, Sarah, telling each other weâ€™d be the first female Hamish and Andy and everyone would love us and weâ€™d be radio stars; I didnâ€™t remember this until I found the notes during my time at AFTRS. How the universe works right? I decided from then on this wasnâ€™t just a really fun job - this is it, Iâ€™m on the right path for my career and I didnâ€™t even know it. I recently moved from breakfast to day time. Itâ€™s a story I canâ€™t be bothered getting into, but it was harsh and it still hurts. It made radio painful. I always loved day time, but after being a brekkie announcer in the same market for so long Iâ€™d gotten arrogant about where I stood on air. I was pulling my shift on day time wondering â€œwhatâ€™d I do to deserve this? I love day time radio, but I want to be breakfast, thatâ€™s where itâ€™s at!â€ Incorrect. I knew it was a shitty thing to think and a shitty thing to say. I started thinking about radio that I loved growing up, and it wasnâ€™t all Kyle and Jackie O and Hamish and Andy. It wasnâ€™t just the Hot 30 Countdown or Fifi and Jules. It was Ellie Mobbs (Angel.) Thank you - Ellie Mobbs - for evoking an emotion in me that I have remembered for years. You see, some time ago - YEARS AGO - when I was still living in Sydney, Ellie sold a song. The song was My Immortal from Evanescence. She sold the song by emotionally recapping hearing it at her good friends funeral, and remembering her every time the song was on. I have never forgotten that talk break. I never will. (BTW yes, she did have a caller, hello? Sheâ€™s a profesh.) I want to be so raw that 6 years down the track someone can tell me they still remember the break. I had to remember that just because youâ€™re a breakfast announcer asking for an emotional response from a phoner, doesnâ€™t mean as a jock you canâ€™t be emotional for your listener. Honesty doesnâ€™t stop at breakfast. I was brave enough to tell my listeners about waxing my mustache on breakfast radio; my day time listeners should expect nothing less. Sometimes you just gotta remember radio is in you for a reason, you just gotta dig deep and remember your craft.ï¿½ï¿½ (PS I have never met Ellie, so if we ever meet things could be kinda creepy now. Experts contend El Nino is responsible for an early wildfire season thatâ€™s predicted to contribute to an above-normal number of blazes in B.C., the Prairies and the Northwest Territories. 2. While a wildfire that raged for two weeks south of Prince George, B.C., is not unheard of this time of year, its 25,000-hectare size was more comparable to fires that erupted in July and August of last year. 3. A silver lining of a catastrophic fire season in the Northwest Territories last year is that a resultant patchwork of burned areas may act like speed bumps to prevent new fires breaking out. It often takes 10 or more years for the patches to become flammable again. 4. A B.C. fire information officer says people often believe that short bursts of rain drive down the danger rating and are good for preventing wildfires. Instead, the officer says prolonged rainfall is required to wet the finer fuels deep in the ground. 5. So Long, Columbia House. And Thanks for Making Me Cool Itâ€™s easy toÂ romanticize the days of physical media. Iâ€™m just old enough to remember the thrill of tracking down a hard-to-find album in a used CD bin and the pleasure of owning something special. I remember how long a new album seemed to last before it felt â€œstale.â€ I remember sitting down to listen to a new CDâ€”really listen to it, not just play it in the background while I juggled 30 other things. I remember all this, and sure, I miss it sometimes. But thereâ€™s no way I would go back. Because in all honesty, the days of music scarcity sucked. As a teenager living in rural Wyoming, the sort of music I wanted to listen to was hard to come by. And even with a generous allowance, at $15 to $20 a pop, building a CD collection was expensive. Without any way to preview an album before plunking down cash, each CD was a risky investment. I became cool overnight, at least in my own head, and practically for free. Thatâ€™s why Columbia Houseâ€”whose parent company said this week it was filing for bankruptcyâ€”was so amazing. For those who donâ€™t remember, Columbia House was basically a subscription service that gave you 10 CDs or tapes for just one cent when you signed up. In exchange, you agreed to buy a set number of albums at full price over the next year. What this meant in practice: one day I had, like, two bootlegged cassettes in my collection. The next day I had a 10-album collection that included Nine Inch Nails, Nirvana, Machines of Loving Grace, and The Cure. I became cool overnight, at least in my own head, and practically for free. That may sound superficial, but getting to sample so many different bands was practically unheard of, short of buying one of those compilation CDs full of pop hits. Even if I wasnâ€™t as cool as the kids in big cities who could find records from indie labels, I was able to find albums by bands like Joy Division, Skinny Puppy, and Ministryâ€”stuff Iâ€™d never have been able to buy at the local Walmart. That was 1995, making me part of the last generation to experience the service before the post-scarcity era of online music. Today my young rural counterparts have smart phones that can stream millions of songs for free, provided theyâ€™re willing to sit through a few ads. Sites like Bandcamp and Soundcloud provide an entire galaxy of obscure indie music to which only people reading the hippest `zines of the old era would ever have been privy. Those kids will never know the joy of opening that first 10-CD bundle, that feeling of being transformed from nerd to hipster in the blink of an eye. But theyâ€™ll also never spend $20 plus shipping and handling to find out an album sucks. That sounds like a fair trade to me. Although we were shocked to hear that the one time giant Columbia House still existed, it is with a small tear that weÂ bid adieu to the company that helped the GREAT Hootie & The Blowfish sell three million extra copies of Cracked Rear View. Ride on Hootie, ride on into the night. You too Columbia records, you tooâ€¦ Â

Collaborator Feature: Adam Lee. Adam Lee is a Telecom Student at Indiana University working primarily within student film productions and also freelance photography/videography. My first interactions with Adam Lee were quite pleasant. Nick and I were over at the coop playing some mellow jams with Neal Anderson and Joe Klatt from Patchwork, sipping on wine, laughing at terrible puns. As we digressed, Adam joined us, snapped some photos, promised to email them later. Well.. we never got themâ€¦ ehhhhrmmâ€¦ but that didnâ€™t damage the interaction! Heâ€™s a great guy:) The Homestead Session Confessional Jump forward like 3 months. Itâ€™s the night before our long anticipated video shoot. Weâ€™re sweating, pulling our hairs out. Our videographer just canceled. Sick. In a last-ditch effort to jettison anxiety, we join local musicians Charlie Jesseph and Peter Oren at Runcible for half-price pitchers. Through course of conversation, we remembered our friend Adam Lee and his background in telecommunications. After a quick call and some coordinating, we had our savior! Adam Lee, Adam Lee, ADAM LEE! (chanting dies out, cut, queue video) We are truly indebted to Adam for making this shoot a reality. He skipped a class, checked out about $100k worth of IU equipment from the telecom building, acquired a friend, Bryce Ferendo, to assist, and worked some magic! Alongside good friend and sound engineer Kyle Hoopt, we shot three videos in a span of a few hours, a session we are calling the Homestead Sessions. You can view all three videos from the Homestead Sessions on YouTube, as well as download the audio files FOR FREE on bandcamp. We recently caught back up with Adam Lee via the webs and sent him some questions to fill us in and thus fill you in! He elaborates on favorite gear, his goals, his approach to filmingâ€¦ Itâ€™s all below! Enjoy:) Q & A How do you know Nick and Jake? I know Nick and Jake because they have come by and played at my co-op. What is your goal as a videographer and/or as a telecom student? My ultimate goal is to be a professional director of photography for feature films, documentaries, TV shows, or music videos. How do you plan for your shoots? I try to get as much information about the shoot as I can. ï¿½ï¿½I am a big believer in research and approaching each situation as its own unique problems. ï¿½ï¿½Since shoots can vary so much, doing your homework and coming to set with experience is the best way to approach it. Do you do a lot of freelance work around Btown? I do most of my work within student film productions as well as the random music gigs and pictures anyone needs. Who are you most inspired by? I am most inspired by directors and cinematographers who are working now or who have came before me. Anyone with strong aesthetic and creative inventiveness really inspire me. ï¿½ï¿½Directors like PT Anderson, Stanely Kubrick, Chris Marker are great. ï¿½ï¿½The great cinematographers I admire are Sven Nykvist, Emmanuel Lubzeki, and Michael Slovis. Have you shot any other videos for bands? I have not shot for any other bands. ï¿½ï¿½Mighty Bros were my first! You girlfriend will be helping with our shoot in June, whatâ€™s it like sharing the same passion? It is great to have a partner with similar passions for me because we can teach and inspire each other as well as connect on many levels. ï¿½ï¿½We have worked together a handful of times and when we plan properly it is an effective team. ï¿½ï¿½We also do a lot of our work independent from each other. What was your favorite thing about working with Mighty Brother? I like working with Mighty Brother because they are fun guys who have an intimate sound from what I have heard. ï¿½ï¿½Chill group of guys who are understanding and willing to work with me to get the job done. What is your approach to shooting live music? Besides planning, shooting live music is all about getting enough coverage to work with in the edit. Also sound and video synch is KEY. What is your favorite piece of equipment? My favorite piece of equipment in telecom is probably the package of Cine lens that we have from Canon. They are super fast lens that give a great look to what they are capturing. Whereâ€™s the best place to capture an Adam in the wild? The best place to catch me in the wild is on some lonesome trail, be it desert, mountains, ocean, forest. What is your favorite Beer? My favorite beer has to be Evil Twin Bible Belt. ï¿½ï¿½I had it in a craft beer bar in London and I fell in love with it. ï¿½ï¿½After I looked it up I realized that it was brewed only once so I will probably never have it again! If we were to summon you back from the dead, what 3 items would we have to put in a chalk circle? To summon me from the dead you would need a Chipotle burrito bowl done my way, a bottle of the Evil Twin Bible Belt poured onto my grave, and cologne blessed by Aphrodite herself. What are you looking forward to most this summer? This summer I am taking part in a photography program in Japan so that will be amazing. I have a few experimental short films in mind going there. What is the best way to approach you for video shooting/production advice and services? Or the the best way to contact you? The best way to approach me for video work is know what you want out of the finished product. Coming to me with that in mind I can put my skills and resources to better suit the clientâ€™s needs. Same goes with giving advice: know as best as you can the pertinent details. The best way to contact me is through email: adamlee@indiana.edu or adamlee133@gmail.com Are you working on any exciting projects right now? I am working on finishing up a documentary short about Deniz an opera singer who lived in the co-op with me. Trying to fit her personality and talent into a 5-8 minute doc is challenging! Would you recommend us to a friend? I would recommend you guys to friends who are down with the folkly, fun, and connected vibes your music produces. The Greatest Generation - The Wonder Years Pop-punk isnâ€™t dead. Itâ€™s in its nature not to die. Punk is rebellion, and thereâ€™s always something to be angry about. As for the pop side, people are still going to love singable hooks to latch onto in the mosh pit. So pop-punk isnâ€™t dead.ï¿½ï¿½Instead, itâ€™s a zombie, walking around with holes in its mouth, expired flesh with traces of what used to be alive, well, and far more capable than what it is now. Most artists try not to get bitten. Fall Out Boy is a pop-infected shadow of what they used to be, Green Day canâ€™t seem to remember how to write anything close to a punk song, and blink-182 is tearing at the seams trying to keep making music. And those are just the bands that are still around. But those were the ones you saw on MTV, during the mainstreamâ€™s descent onto the genre looking for the next big thing. The late 90â€²s/early 2000â€²s was the only time you ever heard pop-punk on the radio, but it never asked to belong there. Most people forget that the namesake was the birthright of the Descendants and the Ramones, carried on by the likes of Kid Dynamite and Lifetime through the 90â€²s underground, never asking for a bigger paycheck or a music video like they saw others do. The minority that remembers - ï¿½ï¿½The Story So Far, Fireworks, and yes, the Wonder Years - has kept pop-punk alive and kicking all this time by taking their cues from emo: when the external is dry, look inside for your energy. The Wonder Years prides themselves on two things: honesty and optimism. Those two convictions have always clashed in small ways, contained throughout the songs of their discography (the lightly self-deprecatingï¿½ï¿½â€œHey Thanks,â€ the barely-escaped futility ofï¿½ï¿½â€œLogan Circleâ€), but theyâ€™ve yet to take center stage in the cohesion of an album. The Upsides focused on the optimism that they could find in everyday life, whereasï¿½ï¿½Suburbia Iâ€™ve Given You All and Now Iâ€™m Nothing focused on outing their hometown in the most candid way possible. The Greatest Generation is the long-awaited head-on collision. The title emerges out of what lyricist Dan Campbell does best: reference. On the surface, â€œthe greatest generationâ€ refers to a line spoken by Tom Brokow, who used it to describe those who survived the Great Depression only to go on to fight in WWII. This comes out on May 6th and has the description: â€œfeaturing Vampirella, Dejah Thoris, Red Sonja, Kato, Jungle Girl, and many, many more! The one ladies sword has more metal than her entire set of metal â€œarmorâ€! Combined, these women almostï¿½ï¿½fulfillï¿½ï¿½the entire bingo card! Wow! I was really hoping that this cover would not summarize the content of the book, which is the combining of many great heroines from the Golden Age of comics - but sadly the contents of the book do seem to send a clear message from Dynamite Entertainment: Women are only worth putting in comics if they visually coded as sex objects first: Nostalgia has a massive influence on comics, largely because only a few creative people are involved in making them (compared with video games and movies) and most of them are specialist skill sets. This combined with general risk aversion, means that sadly none of the â€œbigâ€ titles are prone to challenging their old conventions.ï¿½ï¿½ This is particularly disappointing for Dynamite since the company only started in 2005 - but has huge gallery of golden age characters they purchased but have continued to make them generic copies of what made them so unsuccessful they were up for sale. I mean you want to know how generic this cover is? Letâ€™s compare it to another heroine based book J Scott Campbell was recruited to do the cover for: So, while I want to be really excited about having a big story that is a lot of Golden Age heroines getting together, itâ€™s really hard to do that when the art is basically reduces them all down to the same Barbie dolls with the sameï¿½ï¿½â€œHow do we dodge the censors?â€ costume design ideas. I love nostalgia as much as the next comic book fan - but at some point we have to ask what is the point of continuing the art if we donâ€™t really advance it? preprotext: On this day two years ago, I met Abba for the first time, a thin, weary, nameless mare pulled out of a stable in the back of the bush. She had been kept there for at least a year, possibly two. Rats had eaten her tail down to the dock and chewed the back of her heels. Her mane was falling out in clumps. She was wormy, half-starved and thinner than she looked beneath a fluffy dull coat that was covered in bot fly eggs. There were bald patches and scarring the length of her back from the oversized, ill-fitting saddle she was ridden in, and a damaged muscle in her left haunch from being galloped flat out on the beach without any warm up or cool down. But despite all this there was a spark in her eye and a zest for life. I was just there to take pictures of her but as I watched her walking around the field in her new home, I had to admit that she was kind of cute. Seven months later she was mine. Happy eighth birthday, Abba pony. I may never know your real birth date, or what happened to you in the first six years of your life, but I promise that I will never allow you to be starved and ill-treated again. You may be spoiled rotten these days, eating only the best apples, flirting with your many paramours, and having the run of massive fields full of the most fattening grass, but you deserve it, you opinionated little pony mare. You bring joy to everyone who meets you and put smiles on their faces even on awful days. Sweet girl, youâ€™re a spirit of sunshine in my life and you mean the world to me. Love you, Abracadabra.

Muyembe also sees the prize as a way to encourage young Africans studying abroad to return to work. â€œI have made my career in DR Congo, despite all the conflicts my country has known,â€ the researcher said. â€œWe must build up labs and research centres in Africa,â€ he added, â€œso that when the danger arrives, we can stop it in time. The prosecutorâ€™s examination of events on that fateful night is now complete and he said a decision would be made soon on whether Malek, 27, should stand trial on charges of culpable homicide, causing a shipwreck and collusion in illegal immigration. On No-Churn Ice Cream. After seeing a bunch of stuff about no-churn ice cream come up in various places recently, I decided to take a stab at it myself and see what kind of edible mess I could make. I acquired the ingredients. I planned out what I was going to do. This is my story. [Insert â€œLaw & Orderâ€ Chime Here] Like I said, I had come across a number of different No-Churn recipes in a short period of time so I kindaâ€™ winged it. I pulled from a few but the one I had open while I worked was this Instructables right here -> [Link] The recipe for this stuff is dirt simple - One Pint Heavy Cream, One Can (either 14oz or 12oz) Condensed Milk. From that, you have a blank canvas to mess up as much as you want. The vegan version is just as simple with a can of coconut cream (aka - the solids from coconut milk) and some non-dairy milk like almond milk and the like. Thatâ€™s next on my list to try but back to This batch for now. = ) I had a pack of Land â€˜o Lakes White Hot Chocolate kickinâ€™ around from the winter that I wanted to toss in something - be it a baked good or maybe some coffee - and this seemed like the perfect item. I also got some Andes Mints for some tasty texture (and â€˜cause I like having a reason to buy them besides â€œIâ€™m going to eat all of these before I get home.â€). I also picked up the ingredients for the ice cream base. Where I really deviated from the recipes I found was I made it a point to control the sugar content. This was two-fold: 1) I wanted a slightly less sweet base so I could mess around more with the flavors without killing myself and others with sweetness. 2) My uncleâ€™s a diabetic. My aunt more than likely is, too. Theyâ€™ll have access to this once Iâ€™m done so yeah! A good idea to control the sugar level just in case they dig it and blow through it. I got lucky in that I found a store brand condensed milk that ran 17g of sugar where the bigger brands - Eagle Borden, Carnation and Nestle - tended to run in the low to mid-20â€²s. Itâ€™s not much, mind you, but anywhere I can cut without affecting flavor too terribly I had to try. Another thing I looked into was subbing out condensed milk for coconut cream but I was afraid the slight coconut taste could mess with all that chocolate Iâ€™m dropping into this. The white hot chocolate I used is light already, with a flavor akin to a really good vanilla bean than traditional chocolate. Anything too heavy runs the risk of overpower it. I know this from forgetting I had loaded a coffee K-Cup in my coffee machine when I just wanted to use it to boil the water for the hot chocolate. It was a delicious mistake. = ) Anyhoo! Without further adoâ€¦ White Chocolate No-Churn Ice Cream with Mint Chocolate Chunks: - Ingredients One Pint Heavy Cream One 14oz Can Condensed Milk One 1.25 oz Packet Land Oâ€™ Lakes Classic Arctic White Cocoa mix One small package Andes Creme de Menthe candies - Tools Large Glass Mixing Bowl Mixer (Manual or Electric) Spatula Loaf Pan or Other Container (Optional) - Steps Place mixing bowl in freezer â€˜till chilled along with the Andes candy. Remove mixing bowl. Empty white hot chocolate and heavy cream into bowl and combine. Whip to soft peaks. Slowly fold in condensed milk and combine â€˜til uniform in color. Place in freezer for an hour. Use this time to crush Andes into small chucks. Fineness is up to you. Remove ice cream from freezer and fold in candy bits. Place in freezer for about four to six hours in container of choice. Scoop and enjoy. Some folks whipped theirs to stiff peaks. I went to soft at first â€˜cause I was using a manual mixer and my arms were pretty damn tired after 45mins. Why not use an electric hand mixer? â€˜Cause I started this at 11pm while doing laundry and the hand mixer is loud and kindaâ€™ terrible. Having been Years since I last had to fold in a product, my nice soft peaks fell flat and I decided to (Very Carefully) whip more air into it. This may or may not have lead to the end product being fairly thick. I also think the white hot chocolate mix I used helped in that as it was always a fairly thick. Another change Iâ€™d make is using more candy. The Andes were a bit harder to crack than expected but itâ€™s doable. I only used ten out of a pack of twelve and the scoops in that pic tell the tale. Next time, Iâ€™m going to go with the Andes baking chips - both for size, amount and I donâ€™t have to beat â€˜em up before I add them. All in all, a good first try. Going to have to make another attempt laterâ€¦ and put a little more practice into my folding technique. -.-

To Be Situated at the Head of the Avenue. 16 MAR 1882. Austin Daily Statesman. A NEW STATE HOUSE. Our Capitol for the Interim. At a meeting of the capitol board yesterday morning it was decided to erect a building for the use of the state until the completion of the new capitol. The building will be situated at the head of the avenue on the vacant lot opposite the county courthouse. The contract calls for a building not to exceed forty-five thousand ($45,000) dollars, and to be delivered to the state on or before the first day of January, 1883. The structure is to be of brick and stone, with a frontage on the avenue of 115 feet, and to extend back on Mesquite street 100 feet, and to embrace 13,700 square feet of floor; to be three stories high, with plain and substantial brick or stone cornice and aggregate height of not less than forty-five feet; partition walls to be of brick or stone, and all walls to be constructed with flues for stoves. The first floor to be of cement and the second and third floors to be of pine and deadened. It is to be hoped that the building will answer the purpose of construction, and notwithstanding the quick time in which it is to be finished that it will reflect credit on the capitol board, as also the contractor who submits the most favorable bid to the board.
